---
description: "Prisma schema, migrations, and data access"
globs:
  - "backend/prisma/**/*.prisma"
  - "backend/prisma/**/*.ts"
  - "backend/src/**/*.service.ts"
  - "backend/src/**/*.repository.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Backend Prisma Data

- Capture schema changes via migrations; avoid manual SQL edits outside Prisma migrations.
- Select only needed fields (use `select`/`include`) and batch writes when a loop would produce identical queries.
- Wrap multi-step data updates in transactions; let services orchestrate transactions when necessary.
- Keep Prisma queries inside services/repositories and return domain-friendly errors upstream.
- Map persistence errors to HTTP-friendly responses before they leave the backend layer.
